Reminder: Return to Learn Parent Information Meetings are being hosted this Thursday, July 30 at 6 p.m. and Monday, August 3 at 6 p.m. in the auditorium. We are looking forward to seeing you all as we work to bring students back to school safely.

Interstate 35 School PTO/BEEP Club
April 20 at 3:29 PM ·

We’ve been feeling the blues since the school closure announcement and we need some help brightening our mood!

We are inviting all Roadrunner PK - 6th grades to take part in our virtual coloring contest!

1️⃣ Print out the coloring sheets. Using the link at the bottom.
2️⃣ Students color! Make sure to fill out the name and grade.
3️⃣ Parents can help snap a picture and send to the PTO via Facebook messenger or email interstate35pto@gmail.com
4️⃣ Each student may submit up to 5 entries (1 of each different coloring option)

You have 1 week to print, color, and submit your pictures. Next Monday, April 27th, we will compile all entries into grade level albums and post them to our page. After pictures are posted you can like, comment, share your favorite pictures! At the end of 1 week (Monday, May 4th) we will tally up the pictures with the most ‘likes’ The top 3 winners from each grade will win a Casey's General Store gift card where they can purchase a fun treat!

⬇️Use this link to view and print!⬇️
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1sW4rhhd4jjtMTdJoIY8_It5XjqUq4Jd2k-9iZpUZkuw

Hey everyone!

The I-35 elementary teachers really miss our classroom kiddos! We’ve been seeing posts about teachers driving through town to see their kids, and we decided we wanted to do that as well!

You can have your kiddos stand on the front porch or in the front yard and wave as we drive by! If you live out of town, it would be awesome if you could find a sidewalk or somewhere to stand in the nearest town, but we also understand the importance of social distancing during this time!

We plan to do this next Wednesday, April 1st.
Here’s the schedule:
1:00- Start in Truro
1:45- St. Charles
2:30 New Virginia

These are rough estimates on times, plan to be ready 10-15 min before and after.

Hope to see as many students faces as possible! ❤️

post_text:
Good news! AmazonSmile is now available in the Amazon Shopping App to all AmazonSmile customers using supported Android devices.
🛒📲
If you are an AmazonSmile customer, you can now support Interstate 35 School PTO/BEEP Club in the Amazon shopping app on your Android device! Simply follow these instructions to turn on AmazonSmile and start generating donations.
If you have the latest version of the Amazon Shopping App,
1️⃣open the App on your Android device.
2️⃣View Settings and select AmazonSmile.
3️⃣Follow the in-App instructions to complete the process.
*If you do not have the latest version of the Amazon Shopping App, update your App.
**AmazonSmile is not currently available for iOS users.

#TeacherRequestTuesday
Mrs. Sand's 4th-grade class was another one of our teacher request approvals during our September meeting!
"We are so thankful for the items that you purchased for us! We have already started using the poetry books and the students are VERY excited to have brand new erasers for our whiteboards and fun dice to practice our math fluency. I have so many fun math games to play and the dice will make it so engaging for the students. Thank you!"

post_text: Do you know a great Interstate 35 teacher that has made an impact on your student(s)? Here is a great way to show that you care. Nominate a great teacher today!
shared_text:
Southridge Mall (1111 E Army Post Rd, Des Moines, IA)
July 15, 2019 at 10:01 AM ·

To show our appreciation for all that they do, we are giving away $500 to a different teacher each week who has made a positive impact on their students, school and community. 👩🏫👨🏫 Nominate a teacher who has stood out to you to enter them for a chance to win our 2019 Standout Teachers Giveaway. By nominating someone, you will also be entered for a chance to win $500 for back-to-school shopping. 🔔 Nominees must teach at a school within a 100-mile radius of one of our participating shopping centers. ‼️ Roadrunner community and families‼️

We have supplied a large amount of chalk and asked teachers and staff to ‘Chalk the Walk’ in front of the school building today in preparation for the first day of school tomorrow.

Now it’s your turn! Any community or family members are invited to come and write a welcome back message or draw a fun picture for students to enjoy as they walk the sidewalk to school.

Chalk will be available on the sidewalk until 8 pm tonight feel free to stop by and write or draw an inspirational message for students to start their year!

post_text: Seniors and families, if you haven’t already check out our parking spot painting event!
shared_text:
Interstate 35 School PTO/BEEP Club‎Senior Parking Spot Painting Day
August 2, 2019 at 10:09 AM ·

❗️❕Tomorrow is the day❕❗️
We will have a short meeting at 10am going over rules and information. After our meeting, we will draw names for students that are there and they will get to pick their spots. If we have your contract and payment but you are not at the event we will draw for your spot by number after everyone in attendance has a spot. (We have 20 contracts already!)

If you haven’t already turned in your contract and money you can do that tomorrow to us. We will have a small registration table set up.

PTO will provide 25 gallons of white paint to cover up old paintings. First come, first serve, only available tomorrow from 10-12 while we are there. We will also have snacks 🍪 and refreshments 🥤 available.

Things you need to remember:
🎨 Paint
🔴 Painters tape
🖌 Paint brushes and other supplies needed
🧹 supplies to clean your spot
🚧 something to block your freshly painted spot off
📝 contract
💰 $20 payment

🛒AMAZON PRIME DAY SHOPPERS:

💻Make sure you are shopping through a web browser using, https://smile.amazon.com/ once there you can select Interstate 35 School PTO/BEEP Club as the non profit you would like to support.
📲Purchases made through the APP won’t transfer to our AmazonSmile account, if you regularly shop through the Amazon app, you could add items to your cart via the app but finish the checkout process on your browser.
💰Helping us in this way, does not add money to your cart or come out of you account, the AmazonSmile Foundation donates 0.5% of your total to us! This is a free, easy way to be involved without donating time or money just enjoy your regular shopping! Any questions please feel free to ask!

Parents & families we have joined forces with EPI to provide you with next year’s school supplies. We have taken grade specific supply lists from the teachers and created custom packed boxes for each student. You can order your supplies now and save money in the fall when all the other back to school lists keep adding up!

📝 paper flyers were sent home with students on Friday. These can be filled out and returned back to school by Friday, May 24th or you can order online by Friday, May 31st.

post_text: We ended Teacher Appreciation Week with a sweet treat. A little sugar boost with soda, candy bars, and granola bars to get through a Friday afternoon. Thank you to everyone that helped to make our teachers feel so loved this week. They truly do an amazing job day in and day out for our kids!
